Cell["1. Introduction", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"33f4bcd6-2441-4844-a396-7a21d7e9a61b"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "This notebook is a tutorial on special relativity based on geometrical \
methods. It draws heavily upon the special \[LineSeparator]relativity \
approach in ",
 StyleBox["General Relativity: A Geometric Approach",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " by Malcolm Ludvigsen (1) and ",
 StyleBox["Spacetime and Euclidean Geometry",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " a paper by Dieter Brill and Ted Jacobson (2). After I first wrote this \
notebook a new paper, ",
 StyleBox["From Einstein's 1905 Postulates to the Geometry of Flat Space-Time",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " by N. David Mermin appeared (6). He presents a nice alternative \
formulation of the equal areas proof which I have used."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.753716944029841*^9},ExpressionUUID->"a0336238-fb5c-4710-a0e7-\
ea05618042f5"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The notebook makes extensive use of graphics and animation to illustrate \
the various concepts. Using geometry and ",
 StyleBox["Mathematica,",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " the algebra is quite minimal. One innovation is to replace the second \
postulate of relativity (The laws of physics are the same for all inertial \
observers) with more specific physical postulates. These postulates are also \
more closely identified with geometric constructions. My hope is that they \
will clarify the structure of spacetime and smooth the path for students."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"3fcd3b34-382e-4cf4-9715-aa126e00349a"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "In this notebook I use the convention that ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"c", "\[Equal]", "1"}]],ExpressionUUID->
  "16f6962b-72e6-4c8a-9d77-67b4e104b222"],
 " where ",
 Cell[BoxData["c"],ExpressionUUID->"1d0d1af2-8b4a-4aa8-9731-a18e792df4cd"],
 " is the velocity of light. So time and space are measured in the same \
units. For ease I will talk about photons when I perhaps should use \
\"massless particles\" or \"anything that travels at the limiting speed\" or \
perhaps 'light pulses'."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"86fc0c13-78bc-4ca4-bd67-7c853132ba8a"],

