Cell[TextData[{
 "The stationary observer is represented by the blue circle. In the animation \
the observer remains stationary but in the spacetime diagram he moves on a \
vertical line through time. The observer has positioned a detector at ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"x", "=", "0.75"}]],ExpressionUUID->
  "cf7b2427-d86a-44aa-867f-14c30e0dcb2d"],
 " to detect some event, say the decay of a radioactive particle at that \
location. This is represented by the reddish box. The observer has a clock \
that displays the time. The detector has a similar clock, set to record the \
time the event occurs. The observer will gather this recorded information \
later. The single event is marked in the upper spacetime plot. Space, x, is \
the horizontal axis and time, t, is the vertical axis. In the animation, time \
is varied from 0 to 2. The event occurs at ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"x", "\[Equal]", "0.75"}]],ExpressionUUID->
  "ea1dc5fb-b13d-41ef-8ce6-1c9eb9de79e0"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"t", "\[Equal]", "1"}]],ExpressionUUID->
  "3c4265e1-f1df-4e6a-b875-7d7ea7dec32f"],
 ". A thin gray line in the spacetime diagram represents a spacetime slice at \
various times. The event is a momentary blip that occurs in only one frame of \
the animation. An event is a mathematical idealization in spacetime just as a \
point is in ordinary space."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"20fa6aa7-7f39-4fa9-8892-641c35482e2f"],

Cell["\<\
We will not show any more detectors in this notebook. Rather, an event will \
usually be defined by the intersection of several particles or observers.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"f05f44bb-c6be-44af-b925-911aa0996b6b"],

Cell["\<\
The time on the observer's clock is used to put a scale on the vertical time \
axis in the upper spacetime diagram. Similarly, distance from the observer is \
used to put a scale on the horizontal spatial axis. We will be much more \
interested in the readings on the observers' clocks than we will be in the \
values of the horizontal and vertical coordinates.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"ceae6dfa-500c-48ff-9b6b-bbf8a1b99b4e"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The analog of a line in the plane is a motion in spacetime. The common name \
for a line or motion in spacetime is a ",
 StyleBox["world line",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ". We have already seen this for a stationary observer. All the world lines \
in this notebook will be straight lines, also sometimes called ",
 StyleBox["inertial lines",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ". The following animation illustrates the inertial line of a particle \
moving at a constant speed in space."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"047e09df-45e0-46c8-95a9-795a40c7374a"],

