Cell["\<\
(You may wish to use the up/down arrow keys here to slow step through the \
animation.) A beginning student in relativity may be surprised that the clock \
readings aren't the same. In the real world they aren't the same and we are \
going to be very interested in these clock readings. The calculation for the \
proper time of the moving observer is shown in Section 3.10 below. In \
principle, all measurements in special relativity can be made by reading \
proper times on various observer's clocks. For example, Section 3.1 shows how \
to measure distance using clock readings. Those clocks, reading proper time, \
are the guts of special relativity physics. Keep your eye on them. Don't be \
distracted by other things.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"427ca066-b974-4bc0-b2a7-d1266932bac9"]
}, Closed]],

