Cell["The postulates of special relativity are (5)...", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"c7399da6-8eb2-4aee-82b3-737dd32fb5dc"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The Postulates of Special Relativity - Time Honored Physicist's Version\n1) \
The speed of light ",
 Cell[BoxData["c"],ExpressionUUID->"bde1118d-2fd9-4231-9f06-8d7399f3d5ad"],
 " (",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"\[Equal]", " ", "1"}]],ExpressionUUID->
  "0adc7eb8-6438-42f6-b528-bed287d2e526"],
 ") is the same in all inertial frames.\n2) The laws of nature are the same \
in all inertial frames."
}], "Text",
 CellFrame->True,
 FontFamily->"Helvetica",
 FontSize->16,
 FontWeight->"Bold",
 FontSlant->"Plain",ExpressionUUID->"dde666b1-652f-4af6-90f4-0a9c324ebe4b"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "This is the time honored formulation. However, the second postulate, also \
sometimes called 'The Principle of Relativity', is not always easy for \
students. It is so broad that it is almost vague. Which law of physics should \
be used? It often comes into a derivation like a ",
 StyleBox["deus ex machina",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " to smooth over a rough point. It is easy for a student to misuse it and \
produce erroneous results. This is perhaps a source of many 'paradoxes'. So I \
am going to replace the second postulate by two, more specific, postulates."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"26846d67-870d-4880-b028-308795afe5ab"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The Postulates of Special Relativity - Fussy Physicist's Version\n1) The \
speed of light ",
 Cell[BoxData["c"],ExpressionUUID->"4a594208-61ab-4c18-9f5e-77b2df4041a1"],
 " (",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"\[Equal]", " ", "1"}]],ExpressionUUID->
  "68ba3ed6-389c-4e70-9f70-e60ed155c54a"],
 ") is the same in all inertial frames.\n2) All other things being equal, a \
physical experiment will produce the same result if performed at a different \
time and/or place.\n3) If two inertial observers exchange light signals they \
will observe the same Doppler effect."
}], "Text",
 CellFrame->True,
 FontFamily->"Helvetica",
 FontSize->16,
 FontWeight->"Bold",
 FontSlant->"Plain",ExpressionUUID->"c0a47ac8-aa21-45a2-88a8-733bdc683c52"],

Cell["\<\
The two alternative postulates refer to direct physical experiments. They \
also have direct interpretations in terms of the geometry of spacetime. There \
is nothing vague about them and they cannot be easily misused. They will be \
directly used in the material that follows. They are sufficient to produce \
the results of special relativity.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"b8b82c4d-42aa-4843-87eb-f4d31630b9c2"],

