Cell[TextData[{
 "Even though the lengths of the light rays are changed they remain at 45\
\[Degree] and hence the velocity of light is invariant. If ",
 Cell[BoxData["e"],ExpressionUUID->"d29ca3f5-416c-442c-ad77-7ac64564b751"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData["f"],ExpressionUUID->"cd2dd6a1-4588-4e8e-a3a1-79c20e100c39"],
 " are the Euclidean lengths of the diagonals of a rhombus then the area is ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   FractionBox["1", "2"], "e", " ", "f"}]],ExpressionUUID->
  "c1570ebb-f8b7-40a6-96dd-67840920e566"],
 " and since we have stretched and squeezed the two diagonals such that their \
product is constant, the area is constant. We will see more about this figure \
in the next Section."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"9cb0374c-8c63-49e6-ab2e-0f0976645e2f"],

