Cell[TextData[{
 "The red light lines form a null cone (cone if they were to be rotated about \
a vertical line through ",
 Cell[BoxData["p"],ExpressionUUID->"36f178b6-64a2-4bf8-a3c0-390911d25ea9"],
 "). The blue region represents the future of ",
 Cell[BoxData["p"],ExpressionUUID->"233283cc-d323-4ee2-a108-91651578e414"],
 ". A particle starting from ",
 Cell[BoxData["p"],ExpressionUUID->"38b27d17-fc3b-4e07-8c15-2649e6b94ac0"],
 " could reach any point in the future region. The green region represents \
the past of ",
 Cell[BoxData["p"],ExpressionUUID->"2babc877-4e28-4e11-8e01-7d695a3ca6ed"],
 ". A particle starting from any point in the past region could reach ",
 Cell[BoxData["p"],ExpressionUUID->"dbfc46aa-4a2f-4fc4-acdf-ae9df1cc4218"],
 ". The grey region represents points that could not reach ",
 Cell[BoxData["p"],ExpressionUUID->"ad32173b-d660-41c4-bdc3-8d374c066a71"],
 " or be reached by a particle starting at ",
 Cell[BoxData["p"],ExpressionUUID->"ff8d5743-150e-4ddc-afff-ce8ceba7fc22"],
 ". It would require a velocity greater than the speed of light."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"1e30c61c-7f79-4995-91ae-af7b402b28ed"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Points that occur in the future or past light cones are called timelike. \
The spacetime separation of any such point from ",
 Cell[BoxData["p"],ExpressionUUID->"c2d9d347-0f33-489c-801e-65c94c556c1b"],
 " is specified as a time interval. Points in the gray region are called \
spacelike. The spacetime distance of any such point from ",
 Cell[BoxData["p"],ExpressionUUID->"6c9b11dc-2cab-4485-a779-73f8defcdb04"],
 " is specified as a distance."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"b2becd7e-4811-4f23-8e3e-7b6528820058"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The black line represents the inertial movement of a particle through the \
point ",
 Cell[BoxData["p"],ExpressionUUID->"2ee742ff-1143-484c-bf0b-d3695396a2bd"],
 ". Just to emphasize again that the Lorentz transformation represents jumps \
from one inertial frame to another, but leaves the structure of spacetime \
unchanged, we animate the above diagram with ",
 Cell[BoxData["k"],ExpressionUUID->"8d347315-3a45-43fa-a384-ca4bfbf92175"],
 " varying from ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"1", "/", "10"}]],ExpressionUUID->
