  SuperscriptBox["\[Tau]", "2"]],ExpressionUUID->
  "f92052a5-075e-45b2-bb9a-268bb4e41f89"],
 " is invariant under the transformations of spacetime and so are Euclidean \
areas. Let's say that for the rest frame the length of the timeline is ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"d", "\[Equal]", 
   RowBox[{"2.5", " ", "inch"}]}]],ExpressionUUID->
  "ea94fcd2-fb4a-4b24-a6c7-43ee1147647a"],
 ". We could then introduce an ",
 StyleBox["ad hoc",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " unit ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"L", "\[Equal]", 
   RowBox[{"2.5", " ", "inch"}]}]],ExpressionUUID->
  "e726bf25-3b9e-4de1-8f9d-a65cc6f640f4"],
 " and proceed to calculate ",
 Cell[BoxData["K"],ExpressionUUID->"9f405c16-30f9-41e6-83bf-b864b263d173"],
 " for our diagram. "
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"ba89751b-28a8-4efe-9b55-9a340e463f03"],

