Cell["3. Applications", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"bd15b96b-325f-4913-8d61-38dad675341b"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["3.1 Measuring Distance and Simultaneity", "Subsection",ExpressionUUID->"a8cf37ff-e8ba-4a97-9e99-51b76186dc47"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Imagine two observers who are motionless with respect to each other. (They \
could exchange photons and observe no Doppler shift to ascertain this.) The \
distance between them can be ",
 StyleBox["defined",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " to be half the time it takes to bounce a photon from the first observer \
(blue) to the second observer (green) and back again (1). We assume that the \
second observer carries a reflector."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"127421ec-a647-4106-8511-3226af98621d"],

