Cell["\<\
We don't need a meter stick to measure distance. The actual measurement is \
done with a clock.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"b6b612b0-9430-4fdc-9778-b70ffec5a055"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The same distance would have been obtained if the green observer had \
bounced a photon off the blue observer. (We could arrive at this by \
reflecting the spacetime diagram about a vertical line at ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"d", "/", "2"}]],ExpressionUUID->
  "3bd58841-acf2-4a74-a81c-4091a76da938"],
 ", one of the permissible transformations.) Since spacetime is invariant to \
translations in space we could translate the blue observer to the position of \
the green observer without change to the clock readings. Therefore their two \
clocks must run at the same rate, although they may be set differently."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"d35146e5-8ebe-4452-b9ae-6619ae718962"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "To synchronize clocks we could first measure the distance, ",
 Cell[BoxData["d"],ExpressionUUID->"8aa9a936-93eb-4512-8d93-599c7bf8f466"],
 ", as above. Then blue sends a message giving his time and a timing photon \
to green. Green then sets his clock so it would read ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox["\[Tau]", "blue"], "+", "d"}]],ExpressionUUID->
  "4b7e52b2-2fc3-412e-ab91-d0a2256208c4"],
 " coincident with the timing photon. Once the blue and green clocks are \
synchronized, blue will say that the reflection event was simultaneous with \
his time ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"t", "\[Equal]", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{
      SubscriptBox["\[Tau]", "1"], "+", 
      SubscriptBox["\[Tau]", "2"]}], ")"}], "/", "2"}]}]],ExpressionUUID->
  "995670ca-86d5-4b43-83c6-2a8334dfe9af"],
 ". These simultaneous events are shown as a gold flash on the diagrams. (You \
may have to slow step the animation to catch the flashes.)"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"5dd2fdf5-6740-4f1e-a92f-bfdf82b3dd04"],

Cell["\<\
One reason that we are happy with this definition is that distances should \
add, and they do.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"8e73157d-740d-4112-b066-36642de3cc73"],

