Cell["\<\
Of course, bouncing electromagnetic waves off objects is nothing more than \
the principle of radar. Laser range finders are used in tracking missiles, \
satellites and in lunar ranging (8), which is a test for many general \
relativistic effects. There are laser devices for measuring short distances. \
Real estate agents use them for measuring room size, but here the time delays \
are so short that interference rather than timing is used to determine the \
distance. Such devices are also used in surveying. In any case, using \
electromagnetic waves to determine distance is common.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"dd8765a9-f58c-4399-9a7d-def11ce1e842"],

Cell["\<\
Let's consider the distance measuring procedure above with the first observer \
equidistant between two parallel observers. Then let's subject spacetime to \
the Lorentz transformation.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"d939d540-c760-415a-9a24-77141d7e700e"],

