Cell[TextData[{
 "The event at ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "\[Tau]"],ExpressionUUID->"0526d975-e095-4da6-a7da-29ff0df238fd"],
 " on the first observer's clock is Lorentz transformed (by a factor ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"k", "\[Equal]", "2"}]],ExpressionUUID->
  "d1fff67a-b1db-4cd9-8b33-dbd786b157b8"],
 " in the diagram) to give the event ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "\[Tau]"],ExpressionUUID->"97c5b8f6-cff4-4de2-a270-79f3bd501c1e"],
 " on the second observer's clock. Drawing a light ray back to the first \
observer gives the intersection at ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "\[Sigma]"],ExpressionUUID->"94ae201e-95d2-468c-931d-a48bed210f7b"],
 " and defines the Bondi triangle shown in yellow. The blue point gives what \
we might call the pivot point in the Lorentz transformation. We first stretch \
the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "\[Tau]"],ExpressionUUID->"7c10213c-a770-4e58-9255-53f845dae3f3"],
 " of the first observer ",
 Cell[BoxData["k"],ExpressionUUID->"782b1e5a-745d-40f1-8929-48fbb2de0db6"],
 " times as far from point ",
 Cell[BoxData["A"],ExpressionUUID->"cf3f74bd-2b89-4362-9a31-9792aa7b67cc"],
 ", which brings us to the pivot point. We then shrink the blue pivot point \
to be ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"1", "/", "k"}]],ExpressionUUID->
  "ec699078-1e14-418b-a44c-9d67e2272add"],
 " times as far from point ",
 Cell[BoxData["C"],ExpressionUUID->"dfd31c71-a208-40ee-8211-687bb34ecfd0"],
 " to give the second observer's ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "\[Tau]"],ExpressionUUID->"f1f6533f-f3f0-430d-923f-c9a1b254ff87"],
 ". Since the pivot point is ",
 Cell[BoxData["k"],ExpressionUUID->"051a361c-c6ff-4e03-b97d-51b9a8394c05"],
 " times as far from point ",
 Cell[BoxData["C"],ExpressionUUID->"8756a9dd-f1ea-4c15-b621-55c8c2bc79a0"],
 " as the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "\[Tau]"],ExpressionUUID->"ccc3b025-557a-41ce-99a3-9d583a401213"],
 " of observer 2, we have ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"OA", "/", "OB"}], "\[Equal]", "k"}]],ExpressionUUID->
  "14d24017-2cfb-4df8-b7a4-3a28d6f495af"],
 ". Triangles ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "OB\[Sigma]"],ExpressionUUID->"beb237f6-d8dc-404f-83ad-35cbb7a12f96"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "OA\[Tau]"],ExpressionUUID->"8ab256b9-821a-4c3e-84b2-d7b5be3432b4"],
 " are similar. Then using translation symmetry on the first observer's line, \
we have ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"\[Tau]", "/", "\[Sigma]"}], "\[Equal]", 
   RowBox[{"OA", "/", "OB"}], "\[Equal]", "k"}]],ExpressionUUID->
  "34f795cc-b8be-4924-a4a7-ea79774028fd"],
 " or ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"\[Tau]", "\[Equal]", 
   RowBox[{"k", " ", "\[Sigma]"}]}]],ExpressionUUID->
  "899082e3-d0d8-47f1-a36e-68f7e0d60523"]
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"874e9771-0c6f-47d1-b264-50baed847b8e"],

