\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"dc0ee5aa-a829-4a34-b1cf-50c8b42276c5"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Just as with the similar proof of the Pythagorean theorem, the pink area \
remains constant while two of the blue triangles are repositioned. One of the \
blue triangles is labeled with base ",
 Cell[BoxData["x"],ExpressionUUID->"b466a472-660b-482f-9b90-2af6a6893ab8"],
 ", side ",
 Cell[BoxData["t"],ExpressionUUID->"32ca9720-6987-4a78-aa8d-382b9978eda9"],
 " and diagonal ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "\[Tau]"],ExpressionUUID->"b700edcd-60c9-4f38-b429-3375260f30bc"],
 ". In the starting diagram the pink area is a Minkowski square built on ",
 Cell[BoxData["t"],ExpressionUUID->"2bf79586-542b-4af6-a096-afae9b7313aa"],
 ". This is just twice the area of the causal domain. In the final diagram we \
have two Minkowski squares, the first built on ",
 Cell[BoxData["x"],ExpressionUUID->"c77b9434-7e10-45cc-b633-3f75b49dc34b"],
 " and the second built on ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "\[Tau]"],ExpressionUUID->"b62a7dc1-9c1d-440e-8423-eb734bc097a2"],
 ". The gray square takes no part in the proof. Using the equal area theorem \
relating the area of the causal domain to the proper time or distance, and \
recognizing that any proportionality factor would simply factor out, we have \
the definition of the interval ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   SuperscriptBox["\[Tau]", "2"], "\[Equal]", 
   RowBox[{
    SuperscriptBox["t", "2"], "-", 
    SuperscriptBox["x", "2"]}]}]],ExpressionUUID->
  "5f8229e8-3784-4ff6-91dc-f3a5badeee92"],
 "."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"0b0daf1f-28ff-454b-941c-293220a2ec06"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The above proof is portrayed in a stationary frame where ",
 Cell[BoxData["t"],ExpressionUUID->"d356cdd4-0038-4516-adf2-c44d1ec2e853"],
 " is vertical and ",
 Cell[BoxData["x"],ExpressionUUID->"16ea6bfa-3f1a-4d85-b765-d9741cef6597"],
 " is horizontal. It is also true in moving frames. All we have to do is \
subject the above diagram to the Lorentz transformation. The animation below \
is the same diagram with a Bondi factor of ",
 Cell[BoxData["1.2"],ExpressionUUID->"e6d24e42-e668-4194-b63f-04e2ed480423"],
 "."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"d6a229b3-aac6-44a3-9367-e65781cd6a37"],

