Cell["\<\
One advantage of this demonstration is that it is done entirely in the xt \
spacetime plane. The derivation is geometric rather than algebraic, for \
example as in Resnick & Halliday (4). The other standard demonstration, as in \
Taylor & Wheeler (3), bounces a photon off a mirror in the y direction while \
the whole apparatus is moving in the x direction. That is slightly more \
complicated and raises the question of why the photon travels at the angle it \
does in the xy-plane.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"af113795-f560-4fa8-bfa4-cda63b91936e"]
}, Closed]],

