Cell[TextData[{
 "The above diagram illustrates another effect, or rather non-effect. Imagine \
that the middle observer is actually an atom that absorbs the photon and then \
immediately reradiates it in the forward direction. Then, no matter how the \
atom is moving, it has no effect on the Doppler shift measured by the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
 "\[Tau]"],ExpressionUUID->"9a618a79-b0b6-49c0-a8bf-6edfa33b9791"],
 " observer. The two intermediate ",
 Cell[BoxData["k"],ExpressionUUID->"5260ead0-2b8e-4c79-b4c1-8b2a5bce7942"],
 " factors may change, depending on the state of motion of the atom, but they \
don't change the overall ",
 Cell[BoxData["k"],ExpressionUUID->"72adb5d8-a7e4-4944-99fe-bda821df512f"],
 " factor."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"1119c692-737d-422a-9d85-eb14d2a3e41d"]
}, Closed]],

